{
  "recipe": {
    "description": "A note on pasta making: if your eggs are small, or if when incorporating the flour you find that your dough is too dry, add a bit of warm water, little by little, until the dough is workable but not wet.\n\nFresh pasta cooks faster than dry! Add to salted boiling water, and stir. Once the pasta floats to the surface, it's cooked.",
    "notes": "Tags: Component, Normal, mushrooms, gorgonzola, creme fraiche, lemons",
    "title": "Mushroom cream sauce",
